{{Infobox person | name = Jessica McKenna | image = | caption = | birth_name = Jessica Ruth McKenna | birth_date = {{birth date|1987|4|18}} (age {{age|1987|4|18}}) | birth_place = Yorba Linda, California | ethnicity = | nationality = [[Americans|American]] | education = | alma_mater = Northwestern University | occupation = Screen actor, voice actor, improvisational comedian | years_active = 2012–present | spouse = | domestic_partner = | children = | parents = | salary = | signature = | website = }}
'''Jessica McKenna''' (April 18, 1987) is an American screen actor, voice actor, and improvisational comedian.<ref name=":2">{{Cite news|url=https://www.austinchronicle.com/daily/arts/2017-03-13/sxsw-comedy-review-comedy-bang-bang/|title=SXSW Comedy Review: Comedy Bang! Bang!|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en-US}}</ref> McKenna trained with [[The Groundlings]] and at the [[Upright Citizens Brigade Theatre]], where she regularly performs. McKenna was one of the stars of Fox's ''[[Party Over Here]]'', alongside [[Nicole Byer]] and Alison Rich, and currently hosts the podcast ''Off Book: The Improvised Musical'' on [[Earwolf]].
==Early life== Jessica McKenna was born in Yorba Linda, CA.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm3490846/|title=Jessica McKenna|website=IMDb|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=https://sfsketchfest2018.sched.com/speaker/jessica_mckenna.1xebtxx8|title=Jessica McKenna's schedule for SF Sketchfest 2018|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref> She received a Bachelor's Degree in Theater from [[Northwestern University]].<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" />
==Career==
=== Theater === McKenna began training at the [[Upright Citizens Brigade Theatre]] after college, and became a regular performer in 2012.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.themarysue.com/interview-party-over-here-jessica-mckenna/|title=Interview: Party Over Here‘s Jessica McKenna Talks Women in Comedy and Her Sweet New Gig|website=www.themarysue.com|language=en|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref><ref name=":3">{{Cite news|url=https://www.cpluscomedy.com/comedy/2017/3/8/improvising-comedy-raps-with-jessica-mckenna|title=Improvising comedy raps with Jessica McKenna|work=C+ Comedy|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en-US}}</ref> She regularly performs with the musical improv house teams, Magic to Do and Baby Wants Candy.<ref name=":4">{{Cite web|url=https://ucbcomedy.com/user/19028|title=Jessica McKenna|website=ucbcomedy.com|language=en|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref> McKenna is also a frequent performer at the Upright Citizens Brigade Theatre's long-running improv show, [[ASSSSCAT]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sfweekly.com/culture/dispatches-from-sketchfest-2018-volume-ii/|title=Dispatches from Sketchfest 2018: Volume II - January 31, 2018 - SF Weekly|date=2018-01-31|work=SF Weekly|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en-US}}</ref><ref name=":4" /> McKenna has performed improv comedy at festivals including [[South by Southwest]], [[SF Sketchfest]], [[Edinburgh Fringe]], the [[Del Close Marathon]], [[Bumbershoot]], and [[Chicago Sketch Fest]].<ref name=":2" /><ref name=":1" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://resumes.breakdownexpress.com/890118-3039814-137|title=JESSICA MCKENNA - Resume {{!}} Omnipop Talent Group|website=resumes.breakdownexpress.com|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bumbershoot.com/comedy-conversation/#/artists-comedy/headliners|title=Comedy & Conversation|website=BUMBERSHOOT|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref>
=== Television, film, and web series === In 2014, McKenna was a regular cast member on Fox's improv-based game show, [[Riot (TV series)|''Riot'']], until its cancellation.<ref name=":0" /> In 2016, McKenna starred alongside fellow UCB alum Nicole Byer and Alison Rich in Fox's sketch comedy show, ''Party Over Here'', which was produced by [[The Lonely Island]] and [[Paul Scheer]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/news/fox-launches-saturday-sketch-comedy-series-party-over-here-from-lonely-island-1201697553/|title=Fox Launches Saturday Sketch Comedy Series ‘Party Over Here’ from Lonely Island|last=Prudom|first=Laura|date=2016-02-04|work=Variety|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en-US}}</ref> ''Party Over Here'' was cancelled after one season.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vulture.com/2016/08/fox-cancels-party-over-here-after-one-season.html|title=Party Over Here Canceled, Never to Be ‘Here’ on Fox Again|work=Vulture|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en}}</ref> McKenna has appeared in episodes of ''[[Modern Family]]'' and [[The Goldbergs (2013 TV series)|''The Goldbergs'']].<ref name=":0" />
McKenna often collaborates with UCB alum Zach Reino. McKenna and Reino have worked together on musical sketches for [[Funny or Die]], [[BuzzFeed]], and [[Nickelodeon]].<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://abc.go.com/shows/serious-music/cast/jessica-mckenna|title=Jessica McKenna {{!}} Serious Music|website=ABC|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref> In 2016, McKenna and Reino wrote and starred together in ABC's web series, ''Serious Music''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://abc.go.com/shows/serious-music|title=Watch Serious Music TV Show - ABC.com|website=ABC|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref>
McKenna also works as a [[Voice Actor|voice actor]]. McKenna voices the lead character, Lennon, on [[Amazon (company)|Amazon's]] ''[[Little Big Awesome]]''.<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" /> It was originally announced that McKenna would voice the lead character on ''[[Billy Dilley's Super-Duper Subterranean Summer]]'', however, she was replaced by [[Aaron Springer]] for unknown reasons.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.animationmagazine.net/tv/disney-xd-announces-billy-dilly-and-country-club/|title=Disney XD Announces ‘Billy Dilly’ and ‘Country Club’|date=2016-03-04|work=Animation Magazine|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/disney-xd-orders-pair-original-872355|title=Disney XD Orders Pair of Original Animated Series (Exclusive)|work=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=2018-06-05|language=en}}</ref>
=== Podcasts === Since 2017, McKenna and Reino have hosted the musical comedy podcast ''Off Book'': ''The Improvised Musical'' on the Earwolf network.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.earwolf.com/show/off-book/|title=Off Book: The Improvised Musical podcast on Earwolf|website=www.earwolf.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref> McKenna is also a regular guest on the podcast version of ''[[Comedy Bang! Bang!]]'', where she is known for characters such as Beth, the [[Power Wheels]] obsessed 8 year old, and This Is Your Boy Troy.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.earwolf.com/show/comedy-bang-bang/|title=Comedy Bang Bang: The Podcast podcast on Earwolf|website=www.earwolf.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-05}}</ref> McKenna has also appeared on ''Improv4Humans, The JV Club,'' and ''Hollywood Handbook.''<ref name=":3" />
